A MAN (25) briefly appeared in the Bushbuckridge Magistrates Court on Thursday, 23 June in connection with the rape of a 62-year-old mkhulu. According to police spokesman Brigadier Selvy Mohlala, the man found the mkhulu relaxing in his home in Ga-Motibidu outside Dwarsloop, Limpopo, on the evening of Monday, 20 June, when he attacked him. “The mkhulu noticed a suspect known to him enter his room and he asked him what he wanted. “The suspect allegedly grabbed the victim, pushed him to the bed and raped him. “After the incident, he took cash belonging to the old man, which was on top of the table and left. The suspect was traced and arrested,” said Mohlala. The suspect was remanded in custody until 1 July for a formal bail application. Mpumalanga police commissioner Lieutenant-General Semakaleng Manamela strongly condemned the shameful incident.